This paper deals with the problem of pebble motion on graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents an algorithmic solution to the problem, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. Additionally, the problem involves the study of graph properties and connectivity, which could place it in the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the problem of pebble motion on graphs has applications in the study of computational complexity (cs.CC), which could also be a relevant sub-category.
